The paper proposes a recurrent extension of the Ladder networks, which is a deep learning architecture for hierarchical latent variable models. The paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed architecture on a wide variety of complex learning tasks that benefit from iterative inference and temporal modeling, including video data, music modeling, and perceptual grouping. These tasks are typically associated with computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
